  "injury__illness_and_employment_details.describe_how_injury_illness_happened_line_1": {
    "answer": "I was assigned to help unload and relocate a pallet of custodial supplies that had been delivered to the back loading area of the Borough Administrative Center on Cushman Street. The loading dock was partially snow-packed and wet from people tracking in snow, and we were trying to move the boxes quickly so they would not get damaged by moisture.",
    "is_open_ended": true
  },
  "injury__illness_and_employment_details.describe_how_injury_illness_happened_line_2": {
    "answer": "Each box weighed approximately 45–55 pounds and contained cleaning chemicals and paper products. I had already moved about 10–12 boxes from the pallet to a rolling cart. When I went to lift another box from about mid-thigh level, I did not pause to reposition my feet and instead twisted at the waist to set it on the cart behind me. As I twisted and extended my arms to place the box down, I felt a sharp, sudden pain in my lower back, followed immediately by a pulling sensation in my right shoulder.",
    "is_open_ended": true
  },
  "injury__illness_and_employment_details.describe_how_injury_illness_happened_line_3": {
    "answer": "Because of the pain, I reflexively tried to drop the box quickly onto the cart, but it slipped off the edge. I grabbed for it with my right hand to keep it from falling to the wet floor, and in doing so I bent my wrist awkwardly backward. The box still partially fell, and I had to let it go. I immediately felt increased pain and stiffness in my lower back and a throbbing ache in my right wrist and shoulder. I had to stop what I was doing and lean against the cart for support for a minute or two.",
    "is_open_ended": true
  },
  "injury__illness_and_employment_details.describe_how_injury_illness_happened_line_4": {
    "answer": "After a short break, I tried to move one more smaller box to see if I could continue, but the pain in my lower back increased and I could not bend properly. At that point, I told my coworker, Jason Miller, that I thought I had hurt my back and shoulder. He advised me to stop working and report it to our supervisor. We then notified my supervisor, Karen McAllister, who instructed me to sit down, fill out an incident report, and go to the occupational health clinic for evaluation.",
    "is_open_ended": true
  },
  "injury__illness_and_employment_details.witness_name_contact_number": {
    "answer": "Jason R. Miller – Facilities Maintenance Technician, (907) 555-4479",
    "is_open_ended": false
  },
